{"key":"post-16164653","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>16164653</id>\n<content>Jars are very lame for agar.&amp;nbsp; They take up ten or more times the space of a petri dish, and are deep which prevents CO2 from being expelled properly.&amp;nbsp; They also cost ten times as much.&amp;nbsp; If you're going to do agar, it soon becomes apparent that you'll have 50 or more plates going for a single strain isolation, and that's a LOT of jars.&amp;nbsp; Use petri dishes, and the disposable are the way to go.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>16164658</next>\n<prev>16164631</prev>\n<first>16164562</first>\n<last>16164761</last>\n<when>1335886304</when>\n<utime>05/01/12 06:31 PM</utime>\n</post>"}